         <abstract>
            <p>In this paper we propose a method to construct shape-preserving C&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; cubic polynomial splines interpolating convex and/or monotonic data. For such given data, the existence or nonexistence of such interpolating splines can be expressed in terms of existence or nonexistence of solutions for a system of linear inequalities in two unknowns.</p>
          </abstract>
